<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-04T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-04T05:00:00-05:00" n="630" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d630">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/458: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-04T18:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            4, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received February 4, 1 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>China requests, pending final tariff revision, a temporary surcharge
                                involving 50 per cent advance in valid basis on present tariff
                                allowing an optional 5 per cent <hi rend="italic">ad valorem</hi> on
                                present Hong Kong valuations on any disputed items. American
                                delegation favorable. Does Department sanction?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>